               Covariances, BNL, July 2011                        4231 1451
Covariances from COMMARA-2.0 were adopted for the Mo isotopes.    4231 1451
Here, new sets of covariances were obtained at BNL in 2010 using  4231 1451
the kernel approach in the resonance region and EMPIRE/KALMAN     4231 1451
analysis of experimental data in the fast neutron region.         4231 1451
Dispersion analysis provided expected uncertainties of the order  4231 1451
of 10% for total, elastic and capture with tendency to increase   4231 1451
above 10 MeV. Some isotopic data are available for all channels   4231 1451
but the results still depend heavily on elemental data. The       4231 1451
EMPIRE/KALMAN analysis was performed using "nuisance" parameters  4231 1451
scaling total and reaction cross sections to account for          4231 1451
systematic uncertainties.                                         4231 1451
